    <date day="24" month="November" year="2025"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>This document removes the requirement introduced in Section 3.1 of
   RFC6052 that the NAT64 Well-Known Prefix 64:FF9B::/96 MUST NOT be
   used to represent non-global IPv4 addresses, such as those defined in
   [RFC1918] or listed in Section 3 of [RFC5735].</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
